{"questionId":"22577382","questionHtml":"<p>Show, by differentiation, that the maximum volume occurs at a value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>θ</mi></math> that satisfies the equation&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>recognizing that derivative is equal to zero (seen at any stage)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></em>(accept <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>)</p>\n<p>(from graph, turning point is a global maximum)</p>\n<p>use of product rule&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo> </mo><mn>24</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mi>θ</mi></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mi>θ</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>24</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mi>θ</mi></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mi>θ</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>120</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mi>θ</mi></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>24</mn><mo> </mo><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mfenced><mi>θ</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mn>24</mn><mo> </mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mfenced><mi>θ</mi></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></em>(or equivalent)<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>substituting&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mfenced><mi>θ</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mfenced><mi>θ</mi></mfenced></math> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong><em>M1</em></strong></p>\n<p>e.g&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>120</mn><mo> </mo><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mfenced><mi>θ</mi></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>24</mn><mo> </mo><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mfenced><mi>θ</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mn>24</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mfenced><mi>θ</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>correct intermediate steps leading to given answer&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong><em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mfenced><mi>θ</mi></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mi>θ</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; AG</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong><em>[6 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22577382","referenceCode":"24M.2.AHL.TZ2.3e","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Show, by differentiation, that the maximum volume occurs at a value of θ that satisfies the equation 2 cos2 θ+5 cos θ-1=0.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"e","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 6]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.6—Stationary points, local max and min","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.9—Differentiating standard functions and derivative rules"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}